> is this actually safe to do? what if somebody runs "set" command and that shows value of all enviroment > variables and the value stays in jenkins log forever?
The Jenkins plugin I use to bind the OAuth token masks the secret in the Console Output, so this should prevent accidental leakage. 

@ctiller PTAL - I will change run_performance.sh in a future PR after we decide on a good route for performance testing and I verify the results commenting feature works properly with these changes merged. I had to comment out `subprocess.check_call(['git', 'checkout', args.diff_perf])` to get Jenkins to comment on this PR.
